I will be semi-serious. In some isolated parts of the rural South--West Virginia hill country, for example--some of the more canny hill people will obtain semi-domesticated guinea fowl. They keep them around by feeding them. Guinea fowl will not normally enter a henhouse or any other obvious man-made structure. They are about 75% wild. You won't find the eggs because they'll nest in hollow trees. But some of them, if you keep feeding them, will roost in trees in proximity to your home. And at 2am if a flea farts a mile away, all the guinea fowl will start going bugfuck

https://youtu.be/hJii7MeSR8U

>Interesting question.
It's misleading. You can't conjure a picture perfect apple in your mind as if you were looking at it in real life, as that chart tends to imply to people.
1 is most people. Most people are capable of imagining shapes, colors and details. You can imagine entire scenes, so you're 1.
2 means you're incapable of imagining details, it's a hard barrier in your brain.
3 means you're incapable of imagining color. At all.
4 means you're barely capable of imagining shapes.
5 means you lack imagination, full stop. No matter how hard you try you cannot manifest an image in your head.

Aphantasia is a made up disability created by people who purposefully misrepresent how their brains work. They think that you're supposed to literally see that apple as if you were seeing it IRL. That's not how your brain works. That chart is a retardation chart. 1 is the baseline, everything below it is varying stages of brain damage.
